The immediate past governor of Bayelsa State, Henry Seriake Dickson, has congratulated Vice-President, Yemi Osinbajo on his 63rd birthday anniversary. Dickson described Osinbajo as a patriotic Nigerian who had deployed his immense intellect and capacity in the service of God and man. He said in a statement he personally signed that it was not in doubt that Osinbajo had added enormous value to the Federal Government. He said, “I congratulate my own special egbon, the Vice-President of the Federal Republic of Nigeria, His Excellency Prof. Yemi Osinbajo, on his 63rd birthday in the service of this great country. “There is no doubt that Prof. Osinbajo has added enormous value to the Federal Government of which he is a critical part. In spite of the challenges, he has continued to play his sensitive role with equanimity. “My family and I felicitate with him on this special day and pray to God to sustain His blessings of good health and prosperity upon him in the interest of our dear nation.” Copyright PUNCH.
